President Biden has declared a major disaster in North Dakota due to a severe winter storm, snowstorm, and straight-line winds that occurred from November 9 to November 11, 2022. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, as well as the repair or replacement of damaged facilities in seven counties: Dickey, Kidder, Mercer, Nelson, Ransom, Sargent, and Wells. Additionally, federal funding will be available for snow assistance in four of these counties: Kidder, Mercer, Nelson, and Wells. Hazard mitigation measures statewide will also be eligible for federal funding. Kenneth G. Clark has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas, with the possibility of additional designations in the future. For further information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.